  "title": "Can't correctly deploy instantsearch on GitHub pages",
  "body": "I have been trying to fix a problem I face when using instantsearch in my Jekyll blog hosted on GitHub-pages.\r\n\r\nI use instantsearch with infiniteHits widgets and Travis for updating the index.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that on my machine it works fine but when I push everything on GitHub and I access my search page (https://fedemengo.github.io/search/) the search bar disappear and the whole infiniteHits layout seems to break.\r\n\r\nThis is the gist of my files: https://gist.github.com/fedemengo/54d4f4ce47f09caf677fd8eb41f71334, it also encludes the working HTML produced on my machine. I used babel to avoid the problems with the new feature of js but it still doesn't work.\r\n\r\nIt's weird because on my pc works very smoothly.",
